title: Barnet 3-1 York: Match Report
text:
Barnet 3-1 York: Match Report 17 Oct 2015 17:01:00 
comments Josh Clarke marks Barnet debut with goal as York suffer againJosh Clarke's 90th-minute debut goal helped Barnet end their three-game losing streak with a 3-1 success over York.The Brentford loanee slid past York goalkeeper Scott Flinders at the death following second-half goals from Bees pair John Akinde and Michael Gash.Midfielder Michael Coulson had briefly levelled for the visitors in the 80th minute.Bondz N'Gala should have put the hosts ahead in the 20th minute but the unmarked centre-back scuffed wide from 10 yards after being teed up by former Minsterman Gash.Substitute Akinde, who came on in the 51st minute, broke the deadlock eight minutes after his introduction, slotting past Flinders after being played through by Gash.Coulson forced a fine fingertip save from Jamie Stephens with a powerful right-foot drive before levelling with a drilled 20-yarder struck 10 minutes from time.Parity did not last long, however, as Gash smashed a 25-yard free-kick into the bottom right corner two minutes later.New arrival Clarke then raced clear to beat Flinders in the final minute and ensure the visitors' winless run stretched to seven Sky Bet League Two games.
